KCCAns:
Manure and fertilizer: -
Due to long periods of crop ripening, fertilizers and fertilizers are also high, therefore, 20 tons of dung / compost compost should be mixed uniformly before the last plowing of the farm, in addition to 300 kg of nitrogen (650 kg urea ), 85 kg Phosphor, (500 kg single super phosphate) and 60 k Potash (100 kg Muratapaposh) should be used at a rate of hectare. Use full amount of phosphorus and potash during sowing and use the amount of nitrogen as following.
Autumn sugarcane: - Use the amount of Natarajan in the Sharadik sugarcane divided into four equal parts and use it in 30, 90, 120 and 150 days respectively.
Basant sugarcane: In the spring cane, use total amount of nitrogen divided into three equal parts and use it in 30, 90 and 120 days respectively.
        The use of nitrogen fertilizer increases with the use of nitrogen fertilizers in the application of nitrogen in powder and simultaneous protection from termites. 25 kg Zinc sulphate and 50 kg Ferrous sulphate should be used for sowing the zinc and iron micro-elements at the interval of 3 years as basis fertilizers.

Compost and fertilizer: -
Due to long periods of crop ripening, fertilizers and fertilizers are also high, therefore, 20 tons of dung / compost compost should be mixed uniformly before the last plowing of the farm, in addition to 300 kg of nitrogen (650 kg urea ), 85 kg Phosphor, (500 kg single super phosphate) and 60 k Potash (100 kg Muratapaposh) should be used at a rate of hectare. Use full amount of phosphorus and potash during sowing and use the quantity of nitrogen as follows.
Autumn sugarcane: - Use the amount of Natarajan in the Sharadik sugarcane divided into four equal parts and use it in 30, 90, 120 and 150 days respectively.
Basant sugarcane: In the spring cane, use total amount of nitrogen divided into three equal parts and use it in 30, 90 and 120 days respectively.
        The use of nitrogen fertilizer increases with the use of nitrogen fertilizers in the application of nitrogen in powder and simultaneous protection from termites. 25 kg Zinc sulphate and 50 kg Ferrous sulphate should be used for sowing the zinc and iron micro-elements at the interval of 3 years as basis fertilizers
